23/12/2004
TAIPEI, Taiwan -- Albania and Taiwan signed a memorandum of understanding on co-operation in the fight against money laundering, the justice ministry announced on Wednesday (22 December).
Under the agreement, the two countries will exchange intelligence information about suspicious financial deals and will co-operate in efforts to prevent financial crimes.
Albania and Taiwan are members of the Egmont Group, an international organisation which includes the financial intelligence units of different countries.
(Central News Agency - 22/12/04)
